          "date": "2016-07-03 09:41:34.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2525 ldlm: avoid reordered async flock lock and unlock",
        "message": "LU-2525 ldlm: avoid reordered async flock lock and unlock\n\nFor async flock case, the unlock request may be triggered\nbefore related lock RPC handled by the MDT. If such case\nhanppend, it will leave a ldlm lock on the MDT side that\ncannot be released until the client is umount, or the\nclient is evicted by the MDT.\n\nTo avoid the trouble, before sending the flock unlock RPC\nto the MDT, we search related flock ldlm lock locally. If\nit is still in 'lr_enqueueing' list, then means related\nflock lock RPC has not been handled by the MDT yet. Wait\nthere until related lock is handled by the MDT or failed\nor cancelled.\n\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-656\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iec5bb262d668946675c3894ec530c75a7fee2d6a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
